  "text": "If you’re a Samsung or Android fan who’s on the lookout for some pretty tasty deals on devices, then you might want to check out these offers from Metro by T-Mobile’s newest promo. The carrier is offering a range of different wallet-friendly Samsung devices for free when you sign up for one of several plans. For one, new customers can grab four free Samsung Galaxy A15 smartphones with four lines of unlimited talk, text, and 5G data for just $100 per month. Additionally, new and existing customers can take advantage of exclusive deals on February 25th, including a free Samsung Galaxy A35 with Metro Flex Up line activation or addition, a Samsung Galaxy Tab A9+ for a discounted $10 per month tablet line (plus an exclusive clear Metro tote). In case you’re unfamiliar with the devices, the Galaxy A15 features a 6.5-inch AMOLED display with a sharp 1080×2340 pixel resolution, 5G connectivity, a 50-megapixel main camera, 4-8GB of RAM and 128GB of expandable storage. Meanwhile, the Galaxy Tab A9+ packs an 11-inch display with a 90Hz refresh rate and 1920 x 1200 pixel resolution, a Qualcomm Snapdragon 695 processor aided by up to 128GB of expandable storage, all wrapped up in a sleek body with a metal chassis. Finally, the Galaxy A35 comes with a large 6.6-inch screen, up to 128GB of storage (with micro SD card support), 6GB of RAM, and access to all your favourite Android apps and software features. It also comes with an IP67 rating, keeping it safe from light splashes and dusty scenarios.",
